  <p>Legendary Left Bank blend with extraordinary aging potential. Cassis, violet, graphite, with silky tannins.</p>
  
  <h3>Château Pichon Baron 2015 ($120)</h3>
  <p>Exceptional Pauillac with power and elegance. Blackcurrant, cedar, tobacco, firm structure.</p>
  
  <h3>Château Figeac 2014 ($85)</h3>
  <p>Right Bank elegance with Cabernet Franc complexity. Cherry, herbs, spice, refined tannins.</p>
  
  <h3>Château La Conseillante 2012 ($65)</h3>
  <p>Approachable Pomerol with Merlot richness. Plum, chocolate, coffee, velvety texture.</p>

